{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-js","path":"/SoTrade/","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Lifegorithms","author":"Arthur Papailhau"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"e353c16f-1c67-5612-b37b-bc48a66e82ce","html":"<p><em>This article was started before all the stories around Robinhood and $GME GameStop ğŸš€. Iâ€™ll avoid talking about that in this article.<br>\nI will not explain what options trading is in this article, maybe in another one.<br>\nI will not talk about the harmful effect of having a simple app to deal with money.</em></p>\n<p>Iâ€™m a Software Engineer currently working at Uber ğŸš˜ in San Francisco ğŸ‡ºğŸ‡¸.<br>\nIâ€™ll describe my experience with Robinhood, and why/how I had to build my own app to add the features I thought were missing from Robinhood.</p>\n<p>Here is the work in progress app, as of Jan 31st, 2021:</p>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/afe448aa1b20b91de99f739410849503/e8f1b/SoTrade.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 590px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 41.891891891891895%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"SoTrade Overview\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/afe448aa1b20b91de99f739410849503/fcda8/SoTrade.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/afe448aa1b20b91de99f739410849503/12f09/SoTrade.png 148w,\n/static/afe448aa1b20b91de99f739410849503/e4a3f/SoTrade.png 295w,\n/static/afe448aa1b20b91de99f739410849503/fcda8/SoTrade.png 590w,\n/static/afe448aa1b20b91de99f739410849503/efc66/SoTrade.png 885w,\n/static/afe448aa1b20b91de99f739410849503/c83ae/SoTrade.png 1180w,\n/static/afe448aa1b20b91de99f739410849503/e8f1b/SoTrade.png 2246w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<p>Robinhood, for my European friends, is a ~ trading platform. ğŸ’°<br>\nI think itâ€™s a great platform because the UI is simple, pretty, which makes it easy for most of us to start investing/trading.<br>\nIt became famous because 1ï¸âƒ£ <code class=\"language-text\">the UI is simple</code> and 2ï¸âƒ£ <code class=\"language-text\">itâ€™s commission-free</code>.<br>\nNow, a lot of other free trading platforms exist.  </p>\n<p>This article will describe how I use Robinhood, I will list what I think are the missing features and how SoTrade brings solutions.<br>\nI added some technical details describing how I reversed-engineered Robinhood to use their private APIs. ğŸ¤˜</p>\n<h1 id=\"how-do-i-use-robinhood\"><a href=\"#how-do-i-use-robinhood\" aria-hidden class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>How do I use Robinhood?</h1>\n<h2 id=\"stocks\"><a href=\"#stocks\" aria-hidden class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Stocks</h2>\n<p>Whenever I have some cash from a good trade, I buy stocks. Looking at my portfolio, the main company I believe in is Apple ğŸâ€¦<br>\nI do not day trade with Stocks, I rarely look at it. I invest and forget about it.</p>\n<h2 id=\"options\"><a href=\"#options\" aria-hidden class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Options</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Option_(finance)\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Wiki definition</a>: <code class=\"language-text\">An option is a contract that allows a buyer the right to buy or sell an underlying asset or financial instrument at a specified strike price prior to or on a specified date.</code></p>\n<p>I usually day trade with options, or keep up to a week or two.<br>\nI should learn more about leaps. ( = 1 to 3 years out in the future)</p>\n<h2 id=\"debit-spreads\"><a href=\"#debit-spreads\" aria-hidden class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Debit Spreads</h2>\n<p>I discovered this strategy recently, a great risk-managed strategy. Itâ€™s cheaper than options but also your gains are capped. Capped means that you will have a max profit.<br>\nFor instance, if you bet that Apple wil be more than $150, it doesnâ€™t matter if Apple is $150 or $200 at expiration, you will get the same max profit.<br>\nAs opposed to options where your gains are unlimited.</p>\n<h2 id=\"crypto\"><a href=\"#crypto\" aria-hidden class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Crypto</h2>\n<p>I donâ€™t really do that, I have a tiny bit of crypto just to see where it goes.<br>\nI do have some <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dogecoin\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Dogecoin</a> just because there is a doggy on the coin! ğŸ¶</p>\n<p><u>Note:</u><br>\nYou can see that Index funds are missing from this list, itâ€™s because I use <code class=\"language-text\">Fidelity</code> for that. I donâ€™t want to do day trading with it, I want to keep it separate, invest monthly, automatically, not look at it and forget about it.</p>\n<h1 id=\"what-is-sotrade-what-functionalities-and-how-did-i-build-it\"><a href=\"#what-is-sotrade-what-functionalities-and-how-did-i-build-it\" aria-hidden class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>What is SoTrade, what functionalities, and how did I build it?</h1>\n<p>SoTrade is a cross-platform app (iOS, Android) built with <a href=\"https://reactnative.dev/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">React Native</a>.<br>\nI created like a <code class=\"language-text\">widget</code> for every feature that I think Robinhood was missing.<br>\nUsers will be able to go to the settings and only add the one they are interested in.</p>\n<h2 id=\"notifications\"><a href=\"#notifications\" aria-hidden class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Notifications</h2>\n<p>I wish Robinhood had personalized notifications about how my day/week/month went.<br>\nFor instance, <code class=\"language-text\">This week you made $143, way to go!</code>.</p>\n<p>ğŸ‘‰ I built a <a href=\"https://firebase.google.com/docs/functions/schedule-functions\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">CRON system running on Firebase Cloud Functions</a>.<br>\nIt runs every trading day, at pre-market time, market opening time and closing time.<br>\nIt tells me how much I made/lost overnight and how my day went.</p>\n<p>Example of notifications:</p>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/de3393d24f3e46ea7df0eb99d4d650a2/0940f/notification.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 590px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 93.24324324324323%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"Notifications\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/de3393d24f3e46ea7df0eb99d4d650a2/fcda8/notification.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/de3393d24f3e46ea7df0eb99d4d650a2/12f09/notification.png 148w,\n/static/de3393d24f3e46ea7df0eb99d4d650a2/e4a3f/notification.png 295w,\n/static/de3393d24f3e46ea7df0eb99d4d650a2/fcda8/notification.png 590w,\n/static/de3393d24f3e46ea7df0eb99d4d650a2/efc66/notification.png 885w,\n/static/de3393d24f3e46ea7df0eb99d4d650a2/0940f/notification.png 1154w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<p>Once I have access to my Robinhood data, I can really send any useful things: possibilities are endless!</p>\n<h2 id=\"debit-spreads-1\"><a href=\"#debit-spreads-1\" aria-hidden class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Debit Spreads</h2>\n<p>Debit spreads are capped, meaning there is a max profit. The max profit is done when both legs of the options are ITM (In The Money). You get the max profit only at expiration.<br>\nRobinhood doesnâ€™t tell you what is the max profit. Itâ€™s actually not complex to compute it yourself. Itâ€™s not hard at all, I donâ€™t see why Robinhood would not show it!</p>\n<p>I would like more information for Debit Spreads, like the max profit, how far am I from it, etc.</p>\n<p>ğŸ‘‰ SoTrade is giving you all these information!</p>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/44e311c29c7e2808902f1795388b9167/c6ff8/debit-spread.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 590px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 81.75675675675677%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"Debit Spread\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/44e311c29c7e2808902f1795388b9167/fcda8/debit-spread.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/44e311c29c7e2808902f1795388b9167/12f09/debit-spread.png 148w,\n/static/44e311c29c7e2808902f1795388b9167/e4a3f/debit-spread.png 295w,\n/static/44e311c29c7e2808902f1795388b9167/fcda8/debit-spread.png 590w,\n/static/44e311c29c7e2808902f1795388b9167/efc66/debit-spread.png 885w,\n/static/44e311c29c7e2808902f1795388b9167/c6ff8/debit-spread.png 1088w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<h2 id=\"market-hours\"><a href=\"#market-hours\" aria-hidden class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Market hours</h2>\n<p>In the past few months, I lived in different countries and different timezones, and it always takes me some time to get used to the new market opening time.<br>\nA simple timer to indicate when the market opens would be nice. I think this is a me-problem, so I donâ€™t see why Robinhood would build it lol.</p>\n<p>ğŸ‘‰ SoTrade has a widget showing a timer for the next important event, like opening, closing, pre-market time, etc.</p>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/403cddac08cb4a2dfa7c2f9c748067fa/37523/market-opens-monday.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 590px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 40.54054054054054%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"Market hours\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/403cddac08cb4a2dfa7c2f9c748067fa/fcda8/market-opens-monday.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/403cddac08cb4a2dfa7c2f9c748067fa/12f09/market-opens-monday.png 148w,\n/static/403cddac08cb4a2dfa7c2f9c748067fa/e4a3f/market-opens-monday.png 295w,\n/static/403cddac08cb4a2dfa7c2f9c748067fa/fcda8/market-opens-monday.png 590w,\n/static/403cddac08cb4a2dfa7c2f9c748067fa/37523/market-opens-monday.png 720w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    \n\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/af5f2625b1ae3f9e3eca2950c20c679f/5faa8/market-closed.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 590px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 33.78378378378378%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"Market hours closed\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/af5f2625b1ae3f9e3eca2950c20c679f/fcda8/market-closed.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/af5f2625b1ae3f9e3eca2950c20c679f/12f09/market-closed.png 148w,\n/static/af5f2625b1ae3f9e3eca2950c20c679f/e4a3f/market-closed.png 295w,\n/static/af5f2625b1ae3f9e3eca2950c20c679f/fcda8/market-closed.png 590w,\n/static/af5f2625b1ae3f9e3eca2950c20c679f/efc66/market-closed.png 885w,\n/static/af5f2625b1ae3f9e3eca2950c20c679f/c83ae/market-closed.png 1180w,\n/static/af5f2625b1ae3f9e3eca2950c20c679f/5faa8/market-closed.png 1444w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<h2 id=\"pre-market-data\"><a href=\"#pre-market-data\" aria-hidden class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Pre-market data</h2>\n<p>I usually do the same thing before market-opening when I have options: I look at the pre-market of the company, if itâ€™s higher than yesterday, my options should be green. (I made money)<br>\nThis is very repetitive, thus should be automated!<br>\nRobinhood shows pre-market for stocks but not for options, AFAIK.</p>\n<p>ğŸ‘‰ Iâ€™m currently building a system to pull the pre-market data of all my options so that I donâ€™t have to do that manually and display it in a nice UI. ğŸ¥³</p>\n<h2 id=\"portfolio-snapshot\"><a href=\"#portfolio-snapshot\" aria-hidden class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Portfolio snapshot</h2>\n<p>ğŸ‘‰ Itâ€™s actually not a missing feature, but SoTrade does have a summary to tell you how much you have and whatâ€™s the daily change, both in $ and %.</p>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/e98d4ee8332c3e3d5975df32941eed24/f32b7/portfolio-snapshot.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 590px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 45.27027027027027%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"Portfolio Snapshot\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/e98d4ee8332c3e3d5975df32941eed24/fcda8/portfolio-snapshot.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/e98d4ee8332c3e3d5975df32941eed24/12f09/portfolio-snapshot.png 148w,\n/static/e98d4ee8332c3e3d5975df32941eed24/e4a3f/portfolio-snapshot.png 295w,\n/static/e98d4ee8332c3e3d5975df32941eed24/fcda8/portfolio-snapshot.png 590w,\n/static/e98d4ee8332c3e3d5975df32941eed24/efc66/portfolio-snapshot.png 885w,\n/static/e98d4ee8332c3e3d5975df32941eed24/f32b7/portfolio-snapshot.png 1136w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<h2 id=\"login-screen\"><a href=\"#login-screen\" aria-hidden class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Login screen</h2>\n<p>ğŸ‘‰ I built a login screen describing what it does &#x26; showing the Terms of Service.</p>\n<p>This creates an anonymous user on Firebase Firestore, using <a href=\"https://firebase.google.com/docs/auth/web/anonymous-auth\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Firebase Anonymous Auth</a>.<br>\nThe user in database is useful to store the notification APN tokens, the timezone, and the Robinhood account number. I do not store any personal information like name, age or address.</p>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/89d2a9b27d3dcea249e3bd35661b6373/b06ae/login.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 560px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 213.51351351351352%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"Login\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/89d2a9b27d3dcea249e3bd35661b6373/b06ae/login.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/89d2a9b27d3dcea249e3bd35661b6373/12f09/login.png 148w,\n/static/89d2a9b27d3dcea249e3bd35661b6373/e4a3f/login.png 295w,\n/static/89d2a9b27d3dcea249e3bd35661b6373/b06ae/login.png 560w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 560px) 100vw, 560px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<h2 id=\"sign-in-screen\"><a href=\"#sign-in-screen\" aria-hidden class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Sign-in screen</h2>\n<p>ğŸ‘‰ SoTrade has a Sign-in screen working with Robinhoodâ€™s email/password. It can also handle 2FA, it will wait for your passcode to arrive in your phone and ask you to enter it.  </p>\n<p>To manage this sign-in on the backend, Iâ€™m using the NodeJS Framework named <a href=\"https://github.com/aurbano/robinhood-node\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">robinhood-node</a>. (unofficial)</p>\n<p>Robinhood doesnâ€™t have a public API, but they of course do have their own private APIs on <a href=\"https://api.robinhood.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">api.robinhood.com</a>!</p>\n<p>To get those APIs, the only thing to do is to go to <a href=\"https://robinhood.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">robinhood.com</a>, right-click, inspect element, go to the Network tab and start analysing the network calls.<br>\nYou will see all the GET requests, how the authentication is done, thatâ€™s the reverse-enginnering fun part! ğŸ¥³</p>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/01bcad274ed21dbbc98c1e8c4511ee9e/36eca/signin.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 590px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 66.89189189189189%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"Sign in\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/01bcad274ed21dbbc98c1e8c4511ee9e/fcda8/signin.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/01bcad274ed21dbbc98c1e8c4511ee9e/12f09/signin.png 148w,\n/static/01bcad274ed21dbbc98c1e8c4511ee9e/e4a3f/signin.png 295w,\n/static/01bcad274ed21dbbc98c1e8c4511ee9e/fcda8/signin.png 590w,\n/static/01bcad274ed21dbbc98c1e8c4511ee9e/efc66/signin.png 885w,\n/static/01bcad274ed21dbbc98c1e8c4511ee9e/c83ae/signin.png 1180w,\n/static/01bcad274ed21dbbc98c1e8c4511ee9e/36eca/signin.png 1526w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<h2 id=\"authentication-to-robinhood-with-the-token\"><a href=\"#authentication-to-robinhood-with-the-token\" aria-hidden class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Authentication to Robinhood with the token</h2>\n<p>After a successful login, a token will be generated by Robinhood to authenticate future logins.<br>\nThis is very important to have a strong security &#x26; encryption to store this token, because this is the key to your Robinhoodâ€™s account! ğŸ”‘<br>\nYou can do absolutely anything with this token, so it should not get hacked, under any circumstances!  </p>\n<p>Here is how I secure it at the moment ğŸ‘‡</p>\n<p>I generated a random string as a secret key, I store it as an ENV variable on my Firebase Cloud Functions backend. This secret key is not stored anywhere, except in the environment variable.<br>\nIâ€™m using <a href=\"https://cryptojs.gitbook.io/docs/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">CryptoJS.AES</a> to encrypt and decrypt using this secret key.<br>\nOnly the encrypted token is stored on the database so that if hackers succeeds to have access to the database, they will never be able to retrieve the original Robinhood token without the secret key.</p>\n<p>I encrypt using:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">const encryptedToken = CryptoJS.AES.encrypt(token, secretKey).toString();</code></pre></div>\n<p>For every request, I decrypt the token using the following line:  </p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">const decryptedToken = CryptoJS.AES.decrypt(encryptedToken, secretKey).toString(CryptoJS.enc.Utf8);</code></pre></div>\n<p>Please let me know if you see a big security flaw here &#x26; Iâ€™ll work on it!</p>\n<h2 id=\"statistics\"><a href=\"#statistics\" aria-hidden class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Statistics</h2>\n<p>I love statistics, Iâ€™d love to see how well/poor I did compare to S&#x26;P500, or compare to other people like <code class=\"language-text\">Today, you are in the 9% of worst traders</code> or <code class=\"language-text\">Youâ€™re up 9% this week while S&amp;P500 is up 2.3%, yaaay</code>!</p>\n<p>Or just to make it more social: <code class=\"language-text\">Youâ€™re down 1.8% this week while Robinhood users are on average up 0.2%!</code> ğŸ¥³</p>\n<h1 id=\"whats-next-for-sotrade\"><a href=\"#whats-next-for-sotrade\" aria-hidden class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Whatâ€™s next for SoTrade?</h1>\n<p>I donâ€™t even know if Iâ€™m allowed to do that for someone else than my personal use, because Robinhood doesnâ€™t have public APIs.<br>\nSo once Iâ€™m done with the implementation of the features, Iâ€™ll contact Robinhood and ask them if Iâ€™m allowed to publish that app.<br>\nIâ€™d guess that I am allowed because other apps like Wealthfront are also using Robinhoodâ€™s data. So why them and not me?<br>\nThe security risk of storing Robinhood token is indeed a big risk, Iâ€™d need to check that with them.  </p>\n<p>If I publish it one day, Iâ€™d like people to tell me what features they think are missing so that I can add them to SoTrade.<br>\nI have other ideas for a more long term project, but letâ€™s do baby steps and see where it goes!</p>\n<h1 id=\"robinhood-if-you-read-this-i-have-some-more-important-complaints\"><a href=\"#robinhood-if-you-read-this-i-have-some-more-important-complaints\" aria-hidden class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Robinhood, if you read this, I have some more important complaints!</h1>\n<p>Robinhood is often buggy. Sometimes the cancel button doesnâ€™t work right after placing an order.<br>\nOr I receive notifications a few hours after my order was placed. They suffered from their success and it looks like they havenâ€™t succeeded to work the scale.</p>\n<p>Customer support is terrible. They answer a few days after, saying <code class=\"language-text\">Sorry we again had an outage, we canâ€™t do anything.</code>!<br>\nThatâ€™s not good Robinhood, please improve your downtime and have a valid customer support.</p>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/fb533232f5b27a15a5c33c10ea01c712/9d6a9/smth-went-wrong.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 590px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 42.567567567567565%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"Something went wrong\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/fb533232f5b27a15a5c33c10ea01c712/fcda8/smth-went-wrong.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/fb533232f5b27a15a5c33c10ea01c712/12f09/smth-went-wrong.png 148w,\n/static/fb533232f5b27a15a5c33c10ea01c712/e4a3f/smth-went-wrong.png 295w,\n/static/fb533232f5b27a15a5c33c10ea01c712/fcda8/smth-went-wrong.png 590w,\n/static/fb533232f5b27a15a5c33c10ea01c712/efc66/smth-went-wrong.png 885w,\n/static/fb533232f5b27a15a5c33c10ea01c712/c83ae/smth-went-wrong.png 1180w,\n/static/fb533232f5b27a15a5c33c10ea01c712/9d6a9/smth-went-wrong.png 2256w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<p>Seeing this image â˜ï¸ more than once a year is not acceptable!!</p>","timeToRead":9,"frontmatter":{"title":"Reverse engineering Robinhood to create SoTrade","date":"January 31, 2021","spoiler":"SoTrade, your social trading buddy!","category":"project","published":true},"fields":{"slug":"/SoTrade/","langKey":"en"}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/SoTrade/","previous":{"fields":{"slug":"/review-2020/","langKey":"en","directoryName":"review-2020"},"frontmatter":{"title":"2020 - Year in Review"}},"next":null,"translations":[],"translatedLinks":[]}}}